 ### Failure modes
 
 | Condition                                                          | Behavior |
 |---|---|
-| CDC event arrives before `phase:started`                           | Silently skipped; the catch-up scan reprocesses the writ post-seal. |
-| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | No `evaluate` call, no acceptance/decline row, no transition. The dedupe runs inside the scheduler call and counts only non-deferred prior rows — the dependency gate (which runs *before* the scheduler) re-evaluates every tick regardless. |
-| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix; evaluation is skipped (no row, no transition). |
-| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; evaluation skipped. |
-| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue. |
-| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire evaluation is skipped (no decision is applied). |
+| Tick fires before `phase:started`                                  | Fail-loud throw at handler entry (`[reckoner] tick: activeScheduler not resolved …`). Production never trips this; test fixtures get a deterministic loud signal (D8). |
+| Empty candidate set                                                | The handler early-returns after the held-petitions query — no scheduler call, no rows, no errors (D10). |
+| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | The candidate is filtered out before `SchedulerInput` is built (D7). Already-considered writs never reach the scheduler. The dedupe counts only non-deferred prior rows — the dependency gate (which runs *before* the dedupe filter) re-evaluates every tick regardless. |
+| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] tick:` prefix; the **entire tick** is skipped — no rows for any candidate, no transitions. |
+| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped (no rows for any candidate). |
+| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; the stranger decision is ignored, in-scope decisions still apply. |
+| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped — no decision is applied for any candidate. |
 | Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; the decision is ignored. |
 
